-- Hong Kong shares fall as telecoms weaken
-- By Grace Li
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 04:10AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 6 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares declined on Wednesday with investors taking profits on Chinese telecom firms and awaiting direction from major corporate earnings later this month.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed down 0.3 percent at 24,584.13 points. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong slipped 0.3 percent to a two-week low.  The top percentage loser on the Hang Seng was China Unicom <0762.HK>, which sank 5.3 percent after closing on Tuesday at its highest since October 2012. The one-day drop was also its biggest since May 2013. China Mobile <0941.HK> shed 1.3 percent and China Telecom <0728.HK> 2.1 percent.